    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-03-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="175"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Clay</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 31, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> A despatch under the date of March 3 (No. 30) has
                    been received from Mr. Taylor, accompanied by a treasonable communication
                    written by J. P. Benjamin, at Richmond, to L. Q. C. Lamar, which having been
                    intercepted, fell into the hands of Mr. Taylor.</p>
                <p>Please make known to him my thanks for his watchful attention.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>C<hi rend="smallcaps">assius</hi> M. <hi rend="smallcaps">Clay</hi>, Esq.,
                            <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
